rComments: I really enjoyed this course especially because the teacher was supportive, caring, and really wanted the best for her students. She corrected all the assignments herself and gave meaningful comments. The course content was interesting and engaging. The level of work was adequate. This was my favorite graduate course so far.
Great professor. Weekly contributions and two major assignments. Some flexibility with deadlines, within reason. I enjoyed this course.

Wonderful professor and proactively accommodating to all students during a difficult time. Averages 20 pages of reading per week, plus weekly postings and peer responses (separate days), plus two major assignments. Assignments offer topic flexibility. Material is super diverse and interesting, as well as relevant to current challenges in schools.

a very devoted prof, the best I've had so far. She is understanding and helpful, gives crystal clear instructions and offers one-to-one instructions and support for getting the assignments done. would take class with her again.
Good class, great feedback, no textbook just articles. However, you do not receive any grades until near the end of the semester.

Cheryll is the best, highly organized, very helpful, knows her stuff, very clear in her expectations, and gives you great resources so you actually learn stuff. I have taken courses with her again and will continue to do so!
